{"key":"post-9466036","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9466036</id>\n<content>When you see people running a 'coolmist' 24/7 it's almost always a wicking type with a wet filter inside, and then they have to go buy an ultrasonic to go along with it.&amp;nbsp; Stay away from that setup.&amp;nbsp; The V400 will flood a small mini-greenhouse if you ran it that long.&amp;nbsp; A cycle timer is best so you can dial it in perfectly.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Even more important is to make sure as you're slowly filling up the mini-greenhouse that you keep trays of damp perlite on any empty shelf space.&amp;nbsp; They'll catch drips and also help to keep the humidity up.&amp;nbsp; Once the greenhouse is completely full of substrates, it's very easy to maintain humidity.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>9465745</prev>\n<first>9465717</first>\n<last>9466036</last>\n<when>1229787566</when>\n<utime>12/20/08 05:39 PM</utime>\n</post>"}